he present volume fills that very conspicuous gap. It is the sort of book that practically every college and university library,as well as many public libraries, will need to own, and it will appeal not only to scholars and students but to non-academic readers of O'Connor, whose numbers are legion. A particular value of the book is that it synthesizes criticism and commentary that is now only available in individual essays that are widely scattered. Robert C. Evans is Professor of English at Auburn University Montgomery. Among his many books is Critical Insights: ShortFiction of Flannery O'Connor (2016).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCriticismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 4aEnglish & American Literature. 4aModern History. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican Author.  aAmerican Literature.  aCritical Reception.  aFlannery O'Connor.  aLiterary Criticism.  aMorality.  aRoman Catholic Faith.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311143106240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787442306?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787442306423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787442306/original  a978-3-11-143106-2  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles